    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-01T18:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-01T18:40:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1363.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-01T19:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dominican Government does not agree to raising blockade, as such course, without
                    helping customs receipts, in fact derived from interior towns reached by rail
                    from Puerto Plata, would rehabilitate insurrectionists so that end of war, which
                    they claim is now in sight, would be indefinitely prolonged.</p>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs asks you to consider evil consequences that must
                    ensue if insurrectionists are encouraged by such action which, whatever the
                    intention of American Government, in fact amounts to material aid to
                    insurrectionists. Minister for Foreign Affairs asked if it is intention of
                    American Government to prevent Bordas from either blockading, besieging or
                    bombarding rebels in Puerto Plata. He adds if this is intention of American
                    Government Dominican Government despairs of dealing with situation and American
                    Government must take responsibility openly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
